report.Description: Significant damage in the grouting between the structure base and the concrete support has been observed. The most probable causes are mechanical overload, aging, and wear, or even poor application practices during construction or material incompatibility. The damaged grouting will not be able to distribute the loads uniformly to the foundation elements and will fail to brace the anchor bolts properly, generating bending stress in the bolts.
report.Incident: Improper load redistribution from the structure to the foundation element leading to instability and/or overloading.
report.Failure: The failure mechanism is a combination of mechanical overload, aging, and wear due to the harsh operating conditions.
report.Methodology: Remove existing grout and clean the surface thoroughly. Drill a hole on the anchoring plate to pump the grout in the cavity. Follow the grout instructions from the OEM and build an adequate roll off angle.
report.Health: Major injury or health effects: >1 work day lost case; permanent disability
report.DAMAGE2: Moderate damage to equipment and / or facility Loss of production < one week
report.Description_L: Could occur at some time [once per 10 years]
